Assisted living workflow AI challenges: Common pain points include fragmented communication among caregivers, manual scheduling of care tasks, difficulty tracking resident needs in real time, compliance with health regulations, data privacy concerns, lack of real-time insights, alert fatigue, integration with existing EHR systems, limited scalability, and ensuring user adoption among caregivers. Existing solutions: task management platforms, AI-powered scheduling, predictive analytics for health events, integrated dashboards. Best practices: user-centered design, interoperability, compliance with HIPAA, minimal alert fatigue, training and support, iterative deployment.